The `<PLACEHOLDER>` replaces the second occurrence of `if (!path.isAbsolute(options.dest)) {`. This means the block that resolves relative paths to absolute paths now always runs.

For an absolute path like `/tmp/image.jpg`, both original and mutated would call `path.resolve(__dirname, '/tmp/image.jpg')` = `/tmp/image.jpg`. No difference.

For a relative path like `./downloads/image.jpg`, both would resolve it. No difference.

